network_overview: The capture shows mixed 4G/5G control-plane signaling: one Diameter exchange (Cmd-272) completes successfully, while parallel GTP-C bearer-setup attempts fail with cause 128, and PFCP session-establishment requests repeatedly receive "No Resources Available" from the UPF.

observations.finding: Three consecutive PFCP Session-Establishment requests (Msg-50) sent 10 s apart remain unanswered; UPF replies with Msg-51 cause 73 ('No Resources Available') for the first two attempts.
observations.evidence: Pkt 8 (seq 852494) → Pkt 9 cause 73; Pkt 16 (seq 852495) → Pkt 17 cause 73; Pkt 24 (seq 852496) → Pkt 25 cause 73

observations.finding: GTP-C Create Session Request (Msg-0x10) receives Create Session Response with cause 128, indicating bearer rejection.
observations.evidence: Pkt 29 Msg-0x10 TEID 0x00000000 → Pkt 32 Msg-0x11 cause 128 TEID 0x82100328

observations.finding: Diameter Update-Location-Request (Cmd-272) succeeds; answer carries result-code 2001.
observations.evidence: Pkt 6 Cmd-272 session cmg01;...-005d0115 → Pkt 7 Cmd-272 result 2001

root_causes.description: PFCP Session-Establishment responses consistently return cause 73 ('No Resources Available'), proving the UPF (10.130.9.119) has insufficient resources to instantiate new PDU sessions.
root_causes.impact: 5G user-plane setup blocked; subscribers cannot obtain data bearers.

root_causes.description: GTP-C Create Session Response carries cause 128, causing MME/S-GW to reject the dedicated bearer/EPS session.
root_causes.impact: 4G bearer setup fails; no user-plane tunnel established.

inconclusive_aspects.reason: No SIP, RTP, or IMS protocols observed
inconclusive_aspects.additional_capture_needed: Capture on Nw-interface or P-CSCF with SIP and RTP to determine call success and audio quality

inconclusive_aspects.aspect: Root cause of UPF resource shortage
inconclusive_aspects.reason: PFCP Node-Report or performance counters not present
inconclusive_aspects.additional_capture_needed: UPF performance logs or PFCP Node-Report messages indicating CPU/memory/TEID pool exhaustion
Vendor documentation or GTP-C error file decode to map cause 128 to human-readable reason

recommendations.action: Check UPF resource pools (TEID, memory, CPU) on 10.130.9.119 and clear or expand them.
recommendations.rationale: Three consecutive PFCP Session-Establishment requests rejected with cause 73 prove resource exhaustion.

recommendations.action: Investigate GTP-C entity returning cause 128 for Create Session Response and align with 3GPP standard cause codes.
recommendations.rationale: Bearer rejection blocks 4G data path; exact reason unknown due to proprietary cause value.

recommendations.action: Enable PFCP Node-Report and performance streaming to proactively monitor UPF resource usage.

session_analysis.signaling_health: Diameter succeeds; GTP-C and PFCP session setups fail with explicit rejection causes.
session_analysis.user_plane_health: No GTP-U or user-plane traffic observed after control-plane rejections.
session_analysis.voice_quality: Not observable at this capture point.
session_analysis.cross_plane_correlation: Control-plane failures prevent any user-plane tunnel creation; thus no data or voice media can flow.
